data.enText: a public festival, usually one that happens at a regular time each year, that involves music and dancing in the streets, for which people wear brightly coloured clothes

data.chText: 当地每年都举行狂欢节。
data.enText: There is a local carnival every year.

data.chText: 激动人心的事物组合；五彩缤纷事物的组合
data.enText: an exciting or brightly coloured mixture of things

simple_means.memory_skill: carn 肉 + ival →〔疯狂吃〕肉的节日 → 狂欢节

tr: a festival marked by merrymaking and processions
having sideshows and rides and games of skill etc.
a frenetic disorganized (and often comic) disturbance suggestive of a large public entertainment
example: it was so funny it was a circus
the whole occasion had a carnival atmosphere

value.def: A carnival is a public festival during which people play music and sometimes dance in the streets.
A carnival is a travelling show which is held in a park or field and at which there are machines to ride on, entertainments, and games.

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, use 英国英语用 funfair

value.def: A carnival of something such as colours or sounds is a bright or exciting mixture of them.

example.ex: The avenues lined with jacaranda trees burst into a carnival of purple.
example.tran: 大街的两旁种着蓝花楹，绽放的花朵汇成一片紫色的海洋。

value.tran: 激动人心的事物的组合;五彩斑斓;八音齐奏

partsOfSpeech.dec: carc〔= carn〕肉 + ass →〔变成〕肉 → 尸体
carn 肉 + age 表行为 →〔把人〕切成肉的行为 → 大屠杀
carn 肉 + al …的 → 肉体的；肉欲的
carn 肉 + ival →〔疯狂吃〕肉的节日 → 狂欢节
carni 肉 + vor 吃 + ous …的 → 食肉类的
carr〔= carn〕肉 + ion 表物 → 腐肉
in 使… + carn 肉 + ate 使… → 使成为肉体状态 → 化身
re 重新 + incarnate 化身 → 使转世化身
